It's very odd how when I played yesterday, I had a ping of 45-50... now this isn't what I usually get and I was really surprised that it 'went back' to this ping. A couple months ago (I think it was when the new summoners rift was put in) My ping jumped from my average 40-50 ping, all the way to 79-90 ping. Now for me, that was quite stressing because I casually lag here and it put me on tilt for quite awhile because it was practically twice the amount I usually played on. The only reason my ping spikes is because of the exchange in our area needs to be fixed, and for some reason whenever someone uploads/uses too much of the bandwidth up, the ping spikes up.

So when I played a game today, I was sadly surprised to see my ping back to 79-90.. so whatever you guys did last night, it was good.. make it go back to how it was... ; ;

If there's anyone who knows how they could fix my problem and somehow make it go back to what it was doing yesterday, then please help me! Thanks~

Cheers Agent Mindstar, I saw on my LoLKing match history that one enemy came back online and won the game 1vs0 >__>

